# Awencode Design System

You are building Awencode. The visual language is inspired by valthos.com — ultra-minimal, high-trust, quietly confident. Think: if Linear and Apple had a baby raised by a Swiss typographer.

## Core Philosophy

- **Restraint over decoration.** Every element earns its place. If in doubt, remove it.
- **Whitespace is a feature.** Generous padding, breathing room between elements. Never crowd.
- **Near-monochrome with functional color.** The palette is grey-scale with surgical color accents that carry meaning (status, action, attention). Color is information, not decoration.
- **Typography does the heavy lifting.** Hierarchy comes from weight, size, case, and spacing — not color or ornament.
- **Quiet confidence.** No gradients-for-the-sake-of-gradients, no shadows-for-depth-theater. The interface feels like it was designed by someone who doesn't need to prove anything.

## Color Tokens

### Light Mode (default)

```css
--bg-primary: #ecedef;        /* cool grey canvas */
--bg-secondary: #f4f5f6;      /* slightly lighter panels/surfaces */
--bg-card: #ffffff;            /* card/elevated surfaces */
--bg-input: #ffffff;           /* form inputs */

--border-default: #d8dadd;    /* standard borders */
--border-light: #e4e5e8;      /* subtle dividers, inner borders */
--border-focus: #1a1a1a;      /* focused/selected state */

--text-primary: #1a1a1a;      /* headings, body, primary content */
--text-secondary: #6b6f76;    /* descriptions, supporting text */
--text-tertiary: #9b9ea4;     /* metadata, labels */
--text-faint: #b8bbc0;        /* placeholders, disabled, hints */

/* Functional accents — use ONLY for status/meaning */
--accent-blue: #4a7fd4;       /* active, in-progress, primary action */
--accent-amber: #c78f2e;      /* warning, review, needs-attention */
--accent-red: #c0392b;        /* error, blocked, destructive */
--accent-green: #3a9d63;      /* success, deployed, confirmed */
--accent-grey: #9b9ea4;       /* neutral, queued, inactive */
```

### Dark Mode

```css
--bg-primary: #111113;        /* deep near-black */
--bg-secondary: #18181b;      /* panels, sidebars */
